\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line Although the evaluator indicated that both Criterion 1 and 2 do not comply with minimum standards\'2C the main concern raised by the evaluator centres on vertical progression. The evaluator rightly pointed out that completion of the postgraduate diploma cannot provide entry into the LLM. The evaluator argues that this cannot be allowed for the following reasons\'3A The admission requirements for an LLM degree is an LLB degree. The two qualifications are linked and require specific knowledge\'2C skills and capabilities of its graduates. If a Law Faculty would like to offer interdisciplinary postgraduate qualifications to non-LLB graduates it is advised that M Phil and\'2For PhD programmes are created for this purpose. \line \line Apart from this singular concern\'2C the evaluator feels positive about the programme. The evaluator states that the Postgraduate Diploma in Insurance Law is in line with UNISA\'E2\'80\'99s Open Distance Learning Plan to develop more online postgraduate programmes to meet the need of working professionals. Comprehensive insurance law training will be provided to postgraduate students to empower students by strengthening and deepening their knowledge of insurance law and practices. It will also enable working professionals to undertake advanced reflection and development by means of a systematic survey of current thinking\'2C practice and literature in insurance law. Although the programme demands a high level of theoretical engagement and intellectual independence it is also concerned with the acquisition of practical knowledge.The modules constituting this Diploma programme are furthermore coherently planned with regard to the purpose and outcome of this qualification and the design of the course will certainly meet the clearly defined objectives of this Diploma programme\'3A to provide students with advanced knowledge\'2C specific skills and applied competence in insurance law and to provide the larger community with skilled postgraduate students in the area of Insurance Law. \line \line The Directorate concurs that the programme should be accredited with conditions. \line \line \line \cell \pard 

